49: /**
50:  * {@code StreamsBuilder} provides the high-level Kafka Streams DSL to specify a Kafka Streams topology.
51:  *
52:  * <p>
53:  * It is a requirement that the processing logic ({@link Topology}) be defined in a deterministic way,
54:  * as in, the order in which all operators are added must be predictable and the same across all application
55:  * instances.
56:  * Topologies are only identical if all operators are added in the same order.
57:  * If different {@link KafkaStreams} instances of the same application build different topologies the result may be
58:  * incompatible runtime code and unexpected results or errors
